="aligncenter wp-image-1419420" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200704-WA0022.jpg?resize=450%2C600&#038;ssl=1" alt="PHOTOS: Flood takes over Abeokuta roads, as residents count losses" width="450" height="600" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200704-WA0022.jpg?resize=225%2C300&amp;ssl=1 225w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200704-WA0022.jpg?resize=768%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200704-WA0022.jpg?resize=44%2C58&amp;ssl=1 44w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200704-WA0022.jpg?resize=146%2C194&amp;ssl=1 146w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200704-WA0022.jpg?resize=98%2C130&amp;ssl=1 98w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200704-WA0022.jpg?w=1125&amp;ssl=1 1125w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Mostly affected areas also include Kuto, Isale -Igbein, Lanfewa, Amolaso, Ijeun-Titun, Ago -Ijesa, Abiola way, Isale Abetu, Sokori, Igbore, Oke Mosan and Isale Make area, all in Abeokuta South and North local government areas of Ogun State. Our Correspondent who visited some of the areas saw residents counting their losses. The popular Ogun river was full to the brim. Also, Vehicles were trapped in the flood while as at press time no life has reportedly been lost. Vanguard James Ogunnaike - Abeokuta Early morning downpour that occurred in Abeokuta metropolis has created palpable fear in the minds of residents of the ancient city. Vanguard gathered that the heavy downpour which started at about 1.15 am on Saturday had destroyed property worth several millions of naira. Among the propertyâ€¦ July 4, 2020 In "News" No fewer than five persons were feared dead and property worth millions of naira destroyed on Friday night, as flood wreaked havoc i